				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well I heard that EQBeastlord.com has sold their soul to yantis.
<br />

<br />
I realize that this is probably old news for all the regulars here, but there are most likely many like myself, who only check the message board about once a week to catch up on all thats happened and stay informed in the happenings of the community.
<br />

<br />
One thing I have to say about EQBeastlord is that the community here was previous very strong and had a lot of great regular posters that were very helpful. The Beastlord community had an edge over most other communities and was the last I expected to sell out.  All those charts and great posts created by others to help are now property of Yantis. 
<br />

<br />
Well to make a long story short, I will not be coming back to these forms as I do not wish to support Yantis' ilk nor the people who sell out to him. I realize that the people who have moved on probably have already done so, but there may be a few reading the left overs of the "drama" and if thats the case, could you please reply to this message with the address of the new beastlord message board that is not supported by Yantis? I would still like to read the helpful information the community provides, but I cannot condon doing so here.
<br />

<br />
Thanks in advance,
<br />
*Salute the old EQBeastlord.com*
<br />

<br />
EDIT: I just read the official statement from OGGA on what happened, I know i know im behind times.. ive been busy recently. my comment doesnt really belong in this message, but since the other thread is locked, ill just add it here and im sorry if it offends anyone. To my understanding OGGA did not mention that he was in such dire need of cash to the moderators or to the community itself, he did not make a poll to see what the community thought of that idea give his situation (showing he values the community he helped create), instead he got $3000 offered and sold out without mention. The story of his family is sad im sure, but there is always a way where there is a will and selling out your friends and your community without even consulting them of the situation is extremely poor taste. I dont know ogga, and im sure his situation was bad, but imho, that does not excuse him for what he has done. I think that the lure of the amount of cash is what made him sell the site, and not the actual DIRE need for the cash alone.. there is always other ways, I myself have been in similar situations. Again, not to offend anyone, just adding my thoughts on the matter, I feel sad when someone sells out other peoples work without consulting them, even after taking donations by loyal users, simply because they maintain the offical position of "form owner". Look at the damage that is already done to the community here, Ahh well.. hopefully the money was worth it. I havent seen any public apology to the community, so i guess that means he isnt sorry for what he did, imho a fitting way to redeem the mistake would be to use that $3000 into starting up another beastlord super site that is seperate from yantis. But who cares? he could duck out of the beastlord community have real money by selling his and other peoples work & time with "no consiquence".. funny thing is, "karma" (or whatever similar thing you believe) has a way of catching up with you, and if sell outs like this dont touch your conscience then perhaps thats why the situation arrived in the first place with the family *shrugs*.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
