				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well, I finally might get something off my chest which I thought was going to stay there.
<br />

<br />
I'm staying.  I went back and forth about whether to go to the other site over this one, and it came down to I agree completely with OAGA's descision to sell the site.  It's real easy to say, "hey I would have given money to keep the site the way it was!"  But based on the fact that donations didn't keep up with the cost of the site in the first place, I wouldn't have counted on being able to pull together the money required in the short time frame.  I don't have $3000, or more since that amount didn't completely cover the problem, to blow on a GAME.  I'm more along with some of the other posters who don't live with their parents, who have families to support, and use EQ as a cheap way to spend a little free time.  OAGA didn't sell out, he isn't happy with the way things turned out, but for those who haven't been in situations like this, you do the best you can with what you have and get on with your life.  This is a public forum.  The people who post thoughts here don't still own those thoughts after they hit "submit".  Those thoughts are given.  Do you complain when you give someone a car and they sell it to fund their uncle's bone marrow transplant because his insurance won't cover the cost and he would die in 6 weeks otherwise?
<br />

<br />
Stop b*tching about it and get on with your life.
<br />

