				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">What I would have liked to see, other than bruised egos because they were left out of the loop when the deal went down, was a concerted effort to actually do something about the plat farming and artificial inflation of the eq economy.
<br />

<br />
Instead all that left pretty much left and then buried thier heads in the sand, occomplishing nothing but weakening the community.
<br />

<br />
Anyone who sits down and really thinks of a solution however, knows the real answer to the problem is to persuade Sony to take action. It is, afterall, their responsibility to provide us with a balanced game, which includes a balanced economy.
<br />

<br />
That's gonna cost Sony money a resources. Their have to spend money on lawyers, put resources into programming and fixing the loopholes and cheats in game, and so forth. They simply don't want to do that as in reality players may be fighting among themselves over this, no one is fighting with Sony or quiting the game in any numbers to have an impact.
<br />

<br />
Clearly a site and MB needs to be set up as a base of operations, volunteers for lobbying Sony on their boards, spreading the news through the communities, collecting funds for a possible lawsuit againt Sony by the players, planning boycotts and a whole host of other things one could imagine, all of which could have been started by those who left but wasn't, is really what needs to happen.
<br />

<br />
I see no logic in leaving then to do nothing. I see no connection to supporting Yantis unless you press on the ad and actually sell or buy something, and I see even less logic in splintering a community over bruised egos when the truth of the matter that only makes what needs to be done even harder and actually helps people like Yantis because there's no concentrated unity to get Sony to fix the problem.
<br />

<br />
If I had the resources (money) and the time, I would have loved to set up that websight and MB to get things rolling, but I don't. Perhaps someone here does.
<br />

<br />
Those that left certainly did, but they weren't really interested in actually fixing anything. There's not a peep over there on the subject. Therefore I'm not interested in the 'leave and do nothing" idea. I'd rather stay, make the community stronger, and use that strong community to kick start the effort.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
