				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> Do you complain when you give someone a car and they sell it to fund their uncle's bone marrow transplant because his insurance won't cover the cost and he would die in 6 weeks otherwise?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Actually the more accurate comaprison would be such.
<br />

<br />
Would you be upset if someone you thought was your friend had a car, a nice antique car that he sat in his lawn for the entire neighbourhood to see. He even allowed people to work on the car and improve its condition and its value with their hard work and their time. He let some of those people be in "charge" of certain areas of that car, and through this car he formed a community of friends, one that was stronger then any other community similar to it.
<br />

<br />
Then all of the sudden those he gave charge over certain areas of the car, come to do their daily work on their pride, the antique car, only to find the car is suddenly gone. Where did the car go? Oh the owner sold it to microsoft because he needed money really badly. He didnt tell anyone at all in this small community of friends that he had formed, he made no mention that he was in dire need of money, just BOOM sold one day. 
<br />

<br />
THe effects? The community is now split in more then one direction, there are hurt feelings in more then one person, all the work and time that was put into that car from others other then the owner was not rewarded in the least bit and is now properity of th evil empire microsoft so that his sales will increase 0.1%
<br />

<br />
THAT is what the current situation is like. Dont try and fool yourselfs into thinking that some poor step father was in such dire need and Oaga the saviour came along and did what was necessary. Oaga didnt even give the community of "friends" a chance, first option was a sell out, he didnt let them know of what mioght happen, he didnt give them a chance to help donate or fomulate ideas together on how his problem could be solved. There are lots of intelligent people in the beastlord community and Oaga did not bother tapping into any of them for help with his problem. Instead he sold everyones work and benefited soley from it... where is the money for the other mods hard work? what share did they get from making this site great how it use to be? I bet oaga wont bother to show his appreciation and give them a cent.
<br />

<br />
I am disgusted, and its no doubt that so many people left, the community is fractured, and you have ONE person to blame, its not yantis for making an offer, its Oaga, the sell out.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
